# Routing — TanStack Router

## File-Based Routes

Use `@tanstack/router-vite-plugin`. Routes live in `src/routes/`. The plugin generates `routeTree.gen.ts` — never edit manually.

```
src/routes/
├── __root.tsx          # Root layout (header, footer, outlet)
├── index.tsx           # Home → /
├── services.tsx        # → /services
├── services.lazy.tsx   # Lazy component
├── about.tsx           # → /about
├── contact.tsx         # → /contact
└── contact.lazy.tsx
```

## Root Route

```tsx
import { createRootRoute, Outlet, ScrollRestoration } from "@tanstack/react-router";

export const Route = createRootRoute({
  component: () => (
    <>
      <ScrollRestoration />
      <Header />
      <main id="main-content"><Outlet /></main>
      <Footer />
    </>
  ),
  notFoundComponent: () => <NotFoundPage />,
});
```

## Page Routes with Head

```tsx
export const Route = createFileRoute("/services")({
  component: ServicesPage,
  head: () => ({
    meta: [
      { title: "Our Services | AutoPro Garage" },
      { name: "description", content: "Professional auto repair in Athens..." },
    ],
  }),
});
```

## Lazy Routes

Split page components from the initial bundle:

```tsx
// routes/services.tsx
export const Route = createFileRoute("/services")({});

// routes/services.lazy.tsx
export const Route = createLazyFileRoute("/services")({ component: ServicesPage });
```

## Type-Safe Navigation

```tsx
<Link to="/services">Our Services</Link>  // compile-time checked
<Link to="/services" search={{ category: "maintenance" }}>Maintenance</Link>
```

## Type-Safe Search Params

```tsx
interface ServicesSearchParams { category?: ServiceCategory; }

export const Route = createFileRoute("/services")({
  validateSearch: (search: Record<string, unknown>): ServicesSearchParams => ({
    category: Object.values(ServiceCategory).includes(search.category as ServiceCategory)
      ? (search.category as ServiceCategory) : undefined,
  }),
});
```

## Rules

- All routes in `src/routes/`. File-based only.
- `<Link>` from TanStack Router for internal navigation. Never `<a>` or `window.location`.
- Active links: `activeProps`/`activeOptions` with `aria-current="page"`.
- Every route has `errorComponent` or inherits from root.
- Every route defines `head` with title + description (translated via i18n).
- `ScrollRestoration` in root route.
